  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-asparagus-and-pea-risotto/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-asparagus-and-pea-risotto/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-asparagus-and-pea-risotto/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-asparagus-and-pea-risotto/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and your <strong>arborio rice </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and the <strong>vegetable stock</strong>, a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-asparagus-and-pea-risotto/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>When your risotto is nearly cooked, trim the woody ends off your <strong>asparagus</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>trimmed asparagus</strong> to a pot with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain, return to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-asparagus-and-pea-risotto/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the risotto is cooked, add your <strong>soft cheese</strong> and <strong>blanched peas </strong>to the pan with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and gently stir it all together â€“ this is your <strong>cheesy pea risotto</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-asparagus-and-pea-risotto/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> cheesy pea risotto</strong> and top with the <strong>cooked asparagus</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and garnish with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
